{
  "answer": "**Chapter 73 of the *Viṣṇu Smṛti* details the ritual procedure for performing a *śrāddha* (ancestral offering rite).**[^1]\n\nIt covers inviting and seating Brāhmaṇas; selecting mantras based on the type of *śrāddha* (e.g., uncooked, animal, new moon); invoking and dismissing entities; offering oblations, water (*pādya*, *arghya*), food, and *piṇḍas* (rice balls) to ancestors with specific verses; providing gifts and dakṣiṇā; and dismissing the Brāhmaṇas with blessings.[^1]\n\n[^1]: *Viṣṇu Smṛti*, Chapter 73, [/works/unknown-visnu-smrti-27f0d8/73/translation/](https://falsafa.corpus/works/unknown-visnu-smrti-27f0d8/73/translation/).",
